  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Challenging Private Sector Creditors for a People&apos;s Recovery TJNA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Research to build the evidence-base that reveals the increasing role of private creditors in the debt crises that are currently unfolding and its human costs.
2. National campaigns to build public awareness about the role of private creditors in the failed international financial response to the pandemic and the inadequate global debt architecture.
3. Advocacy  facing policymakers at the national, regional and international levels, so that they feel an enhanced sense of urgency to address private creditor participation in debt negotiations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute to building pressure for an international financial architecture and macroeconomic environment that enables a &apos;people&apos;s recovery&apos; from  Covid-19 - one that provides for the fulfilment of human rights and the undertaking of climate action in economies that centre on care, by building evidence of, and communicating, the urgency of the current debt crisis and its devastating human toll, with a focus on private sector debt, which hitherto has not been included in debt relief and restructuring efforts, yet presents significant and growing fiscal and human costs.</narrative>
  </description>
